                                         Kimber Gold Match Details


Kimber machinists and inspectors, along with computerized measuring machines perform over 200 inspections during the manufacturing and assembly process. Any part found to be out of tolerance is discarded. Recently, the manager of our Customer Service Department assembled a pistol from discarded parts and used it in IPSC competition. He won the first match fired with this pistol and still uses it today.

Equaled only by custom pistols from America's finest pistolsmiths, Gold Match models are the finest 1911 pistols ever manufactured. They combine the features of the Custom Target with a stainless steel match grade barrel, premium aluminum match grade trigger, extended ambidextrous thumb safety and double diamond rosewood grips. Finished in a deep polished blue or stainless steel on the flats with satin finishes on the curves, they look as good as they shoot.

Barrels are machined oversized, then fitted by hand to the slide, frame and barrel bushing. This ensures competition-winning accuracy. Still, the incomparable quality of each Gold Match is the result of state-of-the-art manufacturing. For example, Kimber is the only company with the technology to make forged frames from start to finish on computer driven machines. Many pistolsmiths purchase our finished frames and slides due to their unequaled quality.

During manufacturing a frame is mated with a slide. They travel through the factory together and are continually evaluated to make sure every part added is perfectly matched. Following final assembly pistols are mounted on a machine that cycles the slide hundreds of times in rapid succession. The follow up inspection assures that the critical fit between slide and frame meets exacting standards. Then we test fire each one and conduct a final inspection. Kimber follows this testing procedure for every pistol.

While Gold Match pistols are designed for competition, standard features make them ideal for carry and defense. Corners are rounded and blended to prevent snagging. The rear of the slide is relieved so the sight sets low, encouraging the pistol to point naturally. Dependability, the single most important quality in any defensive situation, is second to none. A Gold Match is quite simply the finest full size 1911 pistol you can buy.

Gold Match - All the features of the Custom Target (Details) along with highly polished deep blue finish, match grade stainless steel barrel fitted by hand to spherical match grade barrel bushing, extended ambidextrous thumb safety, select hand checkered double diamond rosewood grips, new premium skeletonized aluminum match grade trigger.

Stainless Gold Match - Identical to the Gold Match, with frame and slide machined from the finest stainless steel forgings. Highly polished finish on flats, satin finish on the curves. Available in .45 ACP and .40 S&W, and by special order in both 9mm and .38 Super. The world's finest production 1911 pistol. 

Barrels are machined from solid forgings on specially designed computer driven machines. Locking lugs are cut with assembled pistol mounted in special fixture for a perfect fit in this critical area, ensuring unequaled accuracy.

All Gold Match and Custom Shop pistols (Details) include the Kimber extended ambidextrous safety and the new premium aluminum match grade trigger. Hand checkered double diamond rosewood grips are standard.

For unequaled accuracy, Gold Match models have stainless steel match grade barrels fitted by hand to spherical stainless steel match grade barrel bushings. Full length guide rod, Wolff springs and dovetail-mounted sights are standard on every Kimber.

Kimber adjustable sight is standard on Target, Gold Match and Super Match. Steel-on-steel click adjustments are responsive and strong. Rebated notch and serrated blade deflect unwanted light.

title: For Sale:  303 BRITISH NEW & USED BRASS & BULLETS
location: Kern River Valley/Bakersfield, California, United States
postcontent:
I no longer have a 303 British rifle, so am getting rid of the remnants of my 303 reloading components.  I have for sale- Two boxes (40 rounds) of new, never fired, empty 303 British WW brass cartridge casings.  Also for sale is one box of once fired 303 Norma brass which I have found to be the best brass for 303 reloading.  The British made their 303 military rifles with slightly oversize chambers so that dirty cartridges could be chambered and fired under battlefield conditions.  However, this allows the 
brass to expand excessively and shortens the life of the brass.  Norma brass holds up better after several reloadings better than other brands.  I also have ten rounds of once fired 303 brass in good condition and should be good for at least one or two more reloadings. Fired brass has been de-primed and ss pin cleaned. I have been very careful to make sure there are no ss pins remaining in the cases and all primer pockets have been checked to be clean for proper primer seating, but some may have stains that do not affect seating. Note: these cases have not been sized, just de-primed for cleaning.  All cases have boxer primer pockets.  I am also including a partial box (23) of 303 British jacketed bullets.  20 are Sierra 180 gr. .311 Spitzers. The other three are pulled bullets. 1 is a Sierra 150 gr. Spitzer.  1 is a Hornady 150 gr. Spitzer and 1 is a Hornady 174 gr. round nose.  I am selling these cases and bullets together and will not separate.

I am able to deliver this to the Bakersfield or Kern River Valley area for no charge. I will also ship this brass for the actual cost of shipping. title: For Trade:  Beretta PX4 Storm .40 S&W w/ 2 Mags
postcontent:
For trade is a like new PX4 Storm .40  This gun has been been well cared for and fired lightly as I use my 9mm and .22 for range practice.  If you shoot competitively, the Beretta PX 4 (full size 40 cal) greatly diminishes snappy recoil due to its rotating barrel and solid build. This improves accuracy as the shooter doesn't get fatigued from constantly controlling recoil. The ergonomics are phenomenal as the Beretta naturally points flat and true. After several practice rounds I have experienced zero FTE/FTF or any other FT's. The DA trigger pull is like butter and the transition to SA doesn't require much thought.
Sights are adequate but can be upgraded to something more competitive.
Highly recommend this Beretta for competition or HD.
